description:
secretx-keyring/Cargo.toml:14-22:

```toml
[dependencies]
secretx-core = { workspace = true }
async-trait = { workspace = true }
inventory = { workspace = true }
keyring = { version = "3", features = ["linux-native", "crypto-rust"] }
tokio = { workspace = true }

[dev-dependencies]
tokio = { workspace = true }
```

`tokio` is listed in both `[dependencies]` and `[dev-dependencies]` with identical specification (`{ workspace = true }`). The dev-dependency line is dead weight — Cargo deduplicates, but the entry sends a misleading signal that some test-only feature is being added. The sibling crate secretx-systemd uses an explicit feature override in dev-dependencies (`tokio = { workspace = true, features = ["fs"] }`) which is the legitimate use case.

For secretx-keyring, the workspace tokio features (`["rt", "sync", "macros"]`) cover both production and test needs — `#[tokio::test]` requires `macros` (already enabled), `spawn_blocking` requires `rt` (already enabled). No additional features are needed.

Resolution: delete lines 21-22 of Cargo.toml. One-line change.
